            "file_path": "/workspace/fault_localization_result.json",
            "new_string": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\"drivers/ata/libata-core.c\"],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\"ata_device_blacklist\", \"ata_dev_blacklisted\", \"ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv\"],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"Samsung 860 EVO SSD is missing from the ata_device_blacklist array (lines 4393-4639). The blacklist uses glob pattern matching via ata_dev_blacklisted() function to identify problematic devices and apply horkage flags. Similar devices (Samsung SSD 840 and 850 at lines 4562-4565) have ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM set to disable queued TRIM. Without this flag, ata_dev_config_ncq_send_recv() at lines 2218-2221 cannot disable queued TRIM support for Samsung 860 EVO. This allows the device to report FPDMA DSM support, causing libata-scsi.c line 3510 to use ATA_CMD_FPDMA_SEND for TRIM, which causes timeouts with ASMedia ASM1062 controller. The fix is to add Samsung 860 EVO (and 860 PRO) to ata_device_blacklist with ATA_HORKAGE_NO_NCQ_TRIM and ATA_HORKAGE_ZERO_AFTER_TRIM flags.\"\n}",
